@bparees @nalind 
I ran through both Docker and Buildah/Podman again this morning.  The memoryswap and memory values are getting set inside the container only when a run command is executed as noted in previous comments for both Docker and Buildah/Podman.  The behavior in this space between Docker and Buildah/Podman is the same.

I noted: https://github.com/openshift/origin/commit/3194e2535b5d6be402d7dbfcb9cd40332b42170a#diff-d488e3020730d073b7ca207de92622a9 which put in a wait to let the "buildah log output stop before the container output starts".   Did this cure the problem?  Can we close this Issue?

@nalind, if not, thoughts on what to poke at next?

this test is still not re-enabled:
https://github.com/openshift/origin/blob/master/test/extended/builds/s2i_quota.go#L60

@adambkaplan do you want to re-enable it in a PR and see if it's working now?  As i recall it was a flake you'll need to test the PR a few times to have confidence.
